text: Josie Green (born 25 April 1993) is a Welsh professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for and captains Tottenham Hotspur F.C. Women of the FA Women's Super League. == Early life == Green was born in Hemel Hempstead, on 25 April 1993. == Club career == Green started her career at Watford F.C. Ladies but in the 2016/17 season she transferred to Tottenham Hotspur. Green was named as the new captain of Tottenham Hotspur Women in August 2020. ==Honours== Tottenham Hotspur * FA Women's Premier League: Championship Play- off Winner: 2016–17 * FA Women's Premier League Southern Division: 2016–17 == References == Category:Welsh women's footballers Category:Living people Category:1993 births Category:Tottenham Hotspur F.C.
